{"link": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2022_Port_Harcourt_stampede", "titulo": "2022 Port Harcourt stampede", "resumo": "<p>On 28 May 2022, 31 people were killed and seven others injured in a <a href=\"/wiki/Stampede\" title=\"Stampede\">stampede</a> at a church event where free food was to be given out. in <a href=\"/wiki/Port_Harcourt\" title=\"Port Harcourt\">Port Harcourt</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Rivers_State\" title=\"Rivers State\">Rivers State</a>, Nigeria.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup>\n</p>", "hash": "-6426280883356781868", "palavras": 3832, "caracteres": 73222}
{"link": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2022_Indian_Premier_League_Final", "titulo": "2022 Indian Premier League Final", "resumo": "<p>The <b>2022 Indian Premier League final</b> was played on 29 May 2022 at the <a href=\"/wiki/Narendra_Modi_Stadium\" title=\"Narendra Modi Stadium\">Narendra Modi Stadium</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Ahmedabad\" title=\"Ahmedabad\">Ahmedabad</a>. It was a <a href=\"/wiki/Day/night_cricket\" title=\"Day/night cricket\">Day/Night</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Twenty20\" title=\"Twenty20\">Twenty20</a> match, which decided the winner of <a href=\"/wiki/2022_Indian_Premier_League\" title=\"2022 Indian Premier League\">2022 season</a> of the <a href=\"/wiki/Indian_Premier_League\" title=\"Indian Premier League\">Indian Premier League</a> (IPL), an annual Twenty20 tournament in India.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup> <a href=\"/wiki/Gujarat_Titans\" title=\"Gujarat Titans\">Gujarat Titans</a> playing their first tournament won the match and the title by defeating <a href=\"/wiki/Rajasthan_Royals\" title=\"Rajasthan Royals\">Rajasthan Royals</a> by seven wickets. Captain of the Titans, <a href=\"/wiki/Hardik_Pandya\" title=\"Hardik Pandya\">Hardik Pandya</a>, was also the <a href=\"/wiki/Player_of_the_match\" title=\"Player of the match\">player of the match</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-3\">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>", "hash": "8849908270345558845", "palavras": 6358, "caracteres": 107656}
{"link": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tara_Air_Flight_197", "titulo": "Tara Air Flight 197", "resumo": "<p><b>Tara Air Flight 197</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">[3]</a></sup> was a scheduled domestic flight operated by <a href=\"/wiki/Tara_Air\" title=\"Tara Air\">Tara Air</a> for <a href=\"/wiki/Parent_company\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Parent company\">parent company</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Yeti_Airlines\" title=\"Yeti Airlines\">Yeti Airlines</a> from <a href=\"/wiki/Pokhara_Airport\" title=\"Pokhara Airport\">Pokhara Airport</a> to <a href=\"/wiki/Jomsom_Airport\" title=\"Jomsom Airport\">Jomsom Airport</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Nepal\" title=\"Nepal\">Nepal</a>. On 29 May 2022, the <a href=\"/wiki/De_Havilland_Canada_DHC-6_Twin_Otter\" title=\"De Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter\">Twin Otter</a> aircraft carrying 22 people (19 passengers and 3 crew members) departed at 9:55 <a href=\"/wiki/Nepal_Standard_Time\" title=\"Nepal Standard Time\">Nepal Standard Time</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/UTC%2B05:45\" title=\"UTC+05:45\">UTC+05:45</a>) and lost contact with air traffic controllers about 12 minutes later at 10:07.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">[4]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-kp1_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-kp1-5\">[5]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Sky1_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Sky1-6\">[6]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-avherald_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-avherald-7\">[7]</a></sup> The wreckage was located 20 hours later on a mountainside. All 22 passengers and crew were killed with all 22 bodies recovered.<sup id=\"cite_ref-bbc_2022-05-31_black_box_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bbc_2022-05-31_black_box-8\">[8]</a></sup> This was Tara Air's second deadly accident on this route, after <a href=\"/wiki/Tara_Air_Flight_193\" title=\"Tara Air Flight 193\">Flight 193</a> in 2016.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">[9]</a></sup>\n</p>", "hash": "570077251861051302", "palavras": 3617, "caracteres": 70006}
{"link": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elizabeth_II", "titulo": "Elizabeth II", "resumo": "<p><b>Elizabeth II</b> (Elizabeth Alexandra Mary; born 21 April 1926)<sup id=\"cite_ref-birthday_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-birthday-1\">[a]</a></sup> is <a href=\"/wiki/Queen_of_the_United_Kingdom\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Queen of the United Kingdom\">Queen of the United Kingdom</a> and 14 other <a href=\"/wiki/Commonwealth_realm\" title=\"Commonwealth realm\">Commonwealth realms</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-constitutional_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-constitutional-3\">[b]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-realms_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-realms-4\">[c]</a></sup>\n</p>", "hash": "-2310915205200055472", "palavras": 40997, "caracteres": 722220}
{"link": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Platinum_Jubilee_of_Elizabeth_II", "titulo": "Platinum Jubilee of Elizabeth II", "resumo": "<p>The <b>Platinum Jubilee of Elizabeth II</b> is being celebrated in 2022 in the <a href=\"/wiki/Commonwealth_of_Nations\" title=\"Commonwealth of Nations\">Commonwealth of Nations</a> to mark the <a href=\"/wiki/Platinum_jubilee\" title=\"Platinum jubilee\">70th anniversary</a> of the accession of <a href=\"/wiki/Elizabeth_II\" title=\"Elizabeth II\">Queen Elizabeth II</a> on 6 February 1952.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup> The celebration plans were formally unveiled in full by <a href=\"/wiki/Buckingham_Palace\" title=\"Buckingham Palace\">Buckingham Palace</a> on 10 January 2022.<sup id=\"cite_ref-bbcfull_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bbcfull-3\">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>", "hash": "-2108773338836206174", "palavras": 49155, "caracteres": 948270}
{"link": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2022_Port_Harcourt_stampede", "titulo": "2022 Port Harcourt stampede", "resumo": "<p>On 28 May 2022, 31 people were killed and seven others injured in a <a href=\"/wiki/Stampede\" title=\"Stampede\">stampede</a> at a church event where free food was to be given out. in <a href=\"/wiki/Port_Harcourt\" title=\"Port Harcourt\">Port Harcourt</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Rivers_State\" title=\"Rivers State\">Rivers State</a>, Nigeria.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup>\n</p>", "hash": "3370910567804640318", "palavras": 3832, "caracteres": 73222}
