{"link": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2022_Indian_Premier_League_Final", "titulo": "2022 Indian Premier League Final", "resumo": "<p>The <b>2022 Indian Premier League final</b> was played on 29 May 2022 at the <a href=\"/wiki/Narendra_Modi_Stadium\" title=\"Narendra Modi Stadium\">Narendra Modi Stadium</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Ahmedabad\" title=\"Ahmedabad\">Ahmedabad</a>. It was a <a href=\"/wiki/Day/night_cricket\" title=\"Day/night cricket\">Day/Night</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Twenty20\" title=\"Twenty20\">Twenty20</a> match, which decided the winner of <a href=\"/wiki/2022_Indian_Premier_League\" title=\"2022 Indian Premier League\">2022 season</a> of the <a href=\"/wiki/Indian_Premier_League\" title=\"Indian Premier League\">Indian Premier League</a> (IPL), an annual Twenty20 tournament in India.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup> <a href=\"/wiki/Gujarat_Titans\" title=\"Gujarat Titans\">Gujarat Titans</a> playing their first tournament won the match and the title by defeating <a href=\"/wiki/Rajasthan_Royals\" title=\"Rajasthan Royals\">Rajasthan Royals</a> by seven wickets. Captain of the Titans, <a href=\"/wiki/Hardik_Pandya\" title=\"Hardik Pandya\">Hardik Pandya</a>, was also the <a href=\"/wiki/Player_of_the_match\" title=\"Player of the match\">player of the match</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-3\">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>", "hash": "-7919047228636441680", "palavras": 6358, "caracteres": 107656}
{"link": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elizabeth_II", "titulo": "Elizabeth II", "resumo": "<p><b>Elizabeth II</b> (Elizabeth Alexandra Mary; born 21 April 1926)<sup id=\"cite_ref-birthday_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-birthday-1\">[a]</a></sup> is <a href=\"/wiki/Queen_of_the_United_Kingdom\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Queen of the United Kingdom\">Queen of the United Kingdom</a> and 14 other <a href=\"/wiki/Commonwealth_realm\" title=\"Commonwealth realm\">Commonwealth realms</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-constitutional_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-constitutional-3\">[b]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-realms_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-realms-4\">[c]</a></sup>\n</p>", "hash": "180262237795176614", "palavras": 40997, "caracteres": 722220}
{"link": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Platinum_Jubilee_of_Elizabeth_II", "titulo": "Platinum Jubilee of Elizabeth II", "resumo": "<p>The <b>Platinum Jubilee of Elizabeth II</b> is being celebrated in 2022 in the <a href=\"/wiki/Commonwealth_of_Nations\" title=\"Commonwealth of Nations\">Commonwealth of Nations</a> to mark the <a href=\"/wiki/Platinum_jubilee\" title=\"Platinum jubilee\">70th anniversary</a> of the accession of <a href=\"/wiki/Elizabeth_II\" title=\"Elizabeth II\">Queen Elizabeth II</a> on 6 February 1952.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup> The celebration plans were formally unveiled in full by <a href=\"/wiki/Buckingham_Palace\" title=\"Buckingham Palace\">Buckingham Palace</a> on 10 January 2022.<sup id=\"cite_ref-bbcfull_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bbcfull-3\">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>", "hash": "8394911401032969689", "palavras": 49155, "caracteres": 948270}
